2076.experiments: co2 enrichment (face), determination of precipitation type and distribution using an dual-polarised x-band radar, irkis soil water monitoring, mountland, snow manipulation, soil warming, stillberg forest thinning, stillberg nutrient addition study,dischma transect
2076.addinfo:
Climate station located near the bottom of the afforestation. 

New instruments were put in place during 2007. For most parameters, there was a period of overlap when both new and old stations collected data (approx. 27/10/2006 to 30/9/2007). Data are available in "stillberg_climate_1975_to_2007" (old station), "stillberg_climate_post_2007" (new station) and "stillberg_climate" (combined, full measurement period). Please see comments in individual sensor pages for more details.
2076.title: Stillberg:Climate

561.Notes: Nine temperature sensors (thermocouples type 105E from Campbell Scientific), grouted in a shallow borehole, measure rock temperatures at different depths down to 4 m every 30 min. The sensors have been producing data since October 2008. A supporting shallow profile in the adjacent soil was installed in June, 2009.  The example data below show the strong drop in rock temperature around first snowfall on 28 October 2008.
561.title: Fieldsite:23d04ac

564.Notes: Two crackmeters (Vibrating Wire, Model 4420 from Geokon) measure opening of two cracks at the surface (x2 and q2). These sensors have been operational since January 2003 and run at a sampling rate of 1 h and 30 min (since August 2008). A thermistor is built in to the sensors for temperature correction. The temperatures of crack q2 show that this crack is covered with snow for most of the winter. Both cracks show closure during warming periods. The example data below is filtered with a 3 days low-pass filter.
564.title: Fieldsite:20b2f56

567.Notes:
Two in-place inclinometers (Vibrating Wire, Model 6300 from Geokon) are installed across discontinuities in the deep boreholes at the Randa rockslide laboratory. Their purpose is to monitor displacement across these discontinuities and to detect temporal changes in the displacement rate. The instruments measure changes in tilt, which allows for computing the horizontal displacement using the base length of the instrument (1.87 m).

The inclinometers have been operational since January 2004. Between 2004 and 2008 they were placed at 68 m and 85 m depth in the 120 m borehole, sb120. These locations were chosen according to periodic inclinometer surveys (red line in Figure), which showed significant displacement across the discontinuities at those depths. The sampling interval in this time period is 1 h.

In August 2008, fiber-optic strain sensors were installed in sb120 and the borehole was grouted to a depth of about 20 m. Thus the inclinometers had to be removed and were replaced at 12 m depth in sb120 and at 33 m depth in the 50 m deep borehole, sb50s. The latter sensor seems to have technical problems and produces somewhat erroneous data. The sampling interval since August 2008 is 30 min.
567.title: Fieldsite:379ceee

758.Notes: Nine temperature sensors (thermocouples type 105E from Campbell Scientific), grouted in a shallow borehole, measure rock temperatures at different depths down to 4 m every 30 min. The sensors have been producing data since October 2008. A supporting shallow profile in the adjacent soil was installed in June, 2009.  The example data below show the strong drop in rock temperature around first snowfall on 28 October 2008.
758.title: Fieldsite:Fbbea4e

759.Notes: Two crackmeters (Vibrating Wire, Model 4420 from Geokon) measure opening of two cracks at the surface (x2 and q2). These sensors have been operational since January 2003 and run at a sampling rate of 1 h and 30 min (since August 2008). A thermistor is built in to the sensors for temperature correction. The temperatures of crack q2 show that this crack is covered with snow for most of the winter. Both cracks show closure during warming periods. The example data below is filtered with a 3 day low-pass filter.
759.title: Fieldsite:E3cd4bc

4051.Notes: Never measured on both old and new stations simultaneously. Old station measured sum precip per hour in mm (1 measurement per hour) until 10/10/2006. New station measurements started on 27/10/2006. Values were cumulative (in mm) for each 24 hr period from 27/10/2006 to 12/9/2007 and have been summed over 10 min only (in mm) since 12/9/2007. "stillberg_climate_1975_to_2007" and "stillberg_climate_post_2007" give values in these original forms. For "stillberg_climate", values from 27/10/2006 to 12/9/2007 have been converted to 10 min sums (to match scale in following period).
4051.title: Stillberg:65775d5

4052.Notes:
Old station (used until 27/10/2006) measured amount of sunlight per hour (values from 0 to 1; one measurement per hour). Original data is found in "stillberg_climate_1975_to_2007".

New station sampled every 10 minutes. Cumulative minutes of sunshine per day was measured from 27/10/2006 to 29/08/2007. Number of minutes of sunshine per 10 min sampling period (non-cumulative) has been measured since 12/9/2007 (values 0-10). Original data is found in "stillberg_climate_post_2007".

For "stillberg_climate": pre-2007 data is unaltered, data from 27/10/2006 to 29/8/2007 are no longer cumulative (matches following period), and post-2007 data have been divided by 60 to be consistent with pre-2007 scale (values 0-0.1667 for each 10 min period).
4052.title: Stillberg:3a4c269

4347.Notes:
Information:

*Film: Kodak TAX  135/36er   400 ASA    S/W-Negativfilm

*Objektiv: Macro NIKOR  60mm auf Stellung 1:1, d.h. Scharfe mit Objekttrager. Dazu das zirkulare Polarisationsfilter 62mm

*Zeit/Blende: Wir hatten Blende fix 22 und Zeitautomat, doch gibt das Probleme mit ganz unterschiedlicher Belichtung auf dem Negativ. Woher ??? Daher unbedingt nachstes Mal eine Messung und dann fix einstellen. Ungefahre Werte: Blende 22  Zeit 1/15..30

*Raster: 2mm Rasterfolie auf Glastrager aufgeklebt verbessern indem auf Kunststoffplatte Raster einfrasen oder sonst etwas schlaues (Filz mit Raster ?)

*Kamera: Nikon F301 mit Fernausloser
